author: Andrew Lopez, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: How the 2015 Nifty 50 fared in college football's Week 5
text:
Every week in the 2015 college football season, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune is going to take a look back at the Class of 2015 – in particular the 2015 Nifty 50.
Here's a look at how the Nifty 50 fared in Week 2 of the 2015 college football season.
Donte Jackson, cornerback, LSU (Riverdale, No. 2) – three tackles, two kickoff returns for 48 yards
Jerry Tillery, defensive tackle, Notre Dame (Evangel, No. 3) – four tackles, one tackle for a loss
Derrius Guice, running back, LSU (Catholic-Baton Rouge, No. 4) – three rushes, 34 yards, one reception, 6 yards
Kirk Merritt, wide receiver, Oregon (Destrehan, No. 5) – one tackle
Nicholas Brossette, running back, LSU (University Lab, No. 15) – three rushes, 18 yards
Dedrick Shy, cornerback, Tulane (Warren Easton, No. 21) – four tackles, two pass breakups
Jalen McCleskey, wide receiver, Oklahoma State (St. Paul's, No. 24) – two rushes, 19 yards, three receptions, 12 yards, one touchdown, two punt returns for 12 yards
Oshea Dugas, offensive lineman, Louisiana Tech (Northside, No. 26) – Started at left guard
Justin Reid, defensive back, Stanford (Dutchtown, No. 30) – one tackle
Malik Eugene, defensive back, Acadiana (Tulane, No. 36) – one tackle
Orlando Bradford, running back, Arizona (Calvary Baptist, No. 37) – two rushes, minus-1 yards
Participated but did not record a stat: Tyron Johnson, LSU (Warren Easton, No. 1); Isaiah Washington, LSU (Karr, No. 10); Deshawn Raymond, TCU (East Jefferson, No. 14); Bry'Kiethon Mouton, LSU (Acadiana, No. 23); Stanley Morgan, Nebraska (St. Augustine, No. 29); Foster Moreau, LSU (Jesuit, No. 32); Shun Brown, Arizona (Calvary Baptist, No. 41)
